video.title: Supernatural
video.synopsis: Siblings Dean and Sam crisscross the country, investigating paranormal activity and picking fights with demons, ghosts and monsters.

episodes.synopsis: Two brothers witness their mother's paranormal death and are trained to fight by their father, who aims to hunt down the thing that killed his wife.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean follow the coordinates in their father's journal and land in Colorado, where they investigate the disappearance of several campers.
episodes.title: Wendigo

episodes.synopsis: In a small town in Wisconsin, Sam and Dean investigate a series of mysterious drownings officially explained as suicides.
episodes.title: Dead in the Water

episodes.synopsis: On TransNational flight 2485, a man possessed by the spirit of the Phantom Traveler causes the plane to crash, leaving only five survivors.
episodes.title: Phantom Traveler

episodes.synopsis: Several high schoolers dare their friend to look into a mirror and repeat a chant, not knowing that this will unleash a series of mysterious murders.
episodes.title: Bloody Mary

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean help Sam's old college buddy after he is accused of a murder he swears he didn't commit.
episodes.title: Skin

episodes.synopsis: In a small town in Iowa, Sam and Dean encounter the infamous "Hook Man," a spirit who kills his victims with a shiny hook that serves as his hand.
episodes.title: Hook Man

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a town's history and find that a new housing development is being built on sacred Native American land.
episodes.title: Bugs

episodes.synopsis: Sam is haunted by a vision of a woman trapped in the brothers' childhood home and convinces a reluctant Dean that they need to go back there.
episodes.title: Home

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate an abandoned sanitarium and discover the patients had revolted against the cruel punishments inflicted by the head doctor.
episodes.title: Asylum

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean finally make contact with their father, but he tells them to stop looking for him and sends them on another ghost-hunting job.
episodes.title: Scarecrow

episodes.synopsis: While battling a demon, Dean is electrocuted, resulting in permanent damage to his heart and leaving him with only a couple of months to live.
episodes.title: Faith

episodes.synopsis: Dean is contacted by his first love, Cassie, a girl who asks him to come to Mississippi to investigate a string of racially motivated murders.
episodes.title: Route 666

episodes.synopsis: Sam has a premonition in which a man is killed, but the murder is made to look like a suicide.
episodes.title: Nightmare

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean head to Minnesota, where a young boy witnesses a man vanishing into thin air.
episodes.title: The Benders

episodes.synopsis: While investigating a mysterious death in Chicago, Sam and Dean run into Meg, who is thrilled to see Sam again.
episodes.title: Shadow

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a house haunted by the ghost of a man who killed his six daughters during the 1930s.
episodes.title: Hell House

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a small town in Wisconsin where children are falling into comas for no apparent reason.
episodes.title: Something Wicked this Way Comes

episodes.synopsis: A young husband and wife are killed in their home shortly after buying an antique painting of a family portrait from around 1910.
episodes.title: Provenance

episodes.synopsis: After a vampire hunter who was John's mentor is murdered, Sam and Dean are surprised when John himself shows up to solve the case.
episodes.title: Dead Man's Blood

episodes.synopsis: After Sam has a vision of a family being attacked, the brothers and their father head to Salvation, Iowa, to save the family in Sam's dream.
episodes.title: Salvation

episodes.synopsis: On a mission to save their father from Meg, Sam and Dean seek help from an old family friend.
episodes.title: Devil's Trap

episodes.synopsis: Sam, Dean and John were left for dead after the Demon plowed a truck into the Impala. Now the surviving family members must face a powerful adversary.
episodes.title: In My Time of Dying

episodes.synopsis: After listening to a message on John's cell phone from a woman named Ellen, Sam and Dean decide to track her down.
episodes.title: Everybody Loves a Clown

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean encounter Gordon, a fellow demon hunter who has been systematically killing vampires in a small town.
episodes.title: Bloodlust

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Sam investigate the murder of a college student who has come back from the dead seeking revenge on those who mistreated her.
episodes.title: Children Shouldn't Play With Dead Things

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean meet Andy, a slacker who has psychic powers of persuasion that he uses to gain favors from people.
episodes.title: Simon Said

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the brutal slayings of blonde women from the same apartment building.
episodes.title: No Exit

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the murder of a lawyer and his wife. Right before they died, they claimed they'd seen a ghost.
episodes.title: The Usual Suspects

episodes.synopsis: When two highly successful professionals die after claiming to be haunted by hellhounds, Sam and Dean investigate a local bar.
episodes.title: Crossroad Blues

episodes.synopsis: When Sam has a vision of Dean killing a young man who seems to be possessed by a demon, the two brothers head to Oregon to search for answers.
episodes.title: Croatoan

episodes.synopsis: After Dean tells Sam what their father told him before he died, the distraught Sam sneaks off to Indiana alone.
episodes.title: Hunted

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate two strange deaths at a small Connecticut inn run by a single mom whose young daughter plays with an imaginary friend.
episodes.title: Playthings

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a string of robberies with a disturbing pattern.
episodes.title: Night Shifter

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the murders of several people by individuals who claim they were visited by an angel and were carrying out God's will.
episodes.title: Houses of the Holy

episodes.synopsis: After receiving a frantic call from Sam, who has been missing for more than a week, Dean races to his brother's side.
episodes.title: Born Under a Bad Sign

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean call on their friend Bobby for help after they are stumped by violent and inexplicable happenings on a local college campus.
episodes.title: Tall Tales

episodes.synopsis: While driving down a deserted road, Sam and Dean are startled when a bloody woman runs in front of the Impala, screaming for help.
episodes.title: Roadkill

episodes.synopsis: While investigating the death of a lawyer who appeared to have been killed by a wild animal, Sam and Dean realize they are tracking a werewolf.
episodes.title: Heart

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean travel to Hollywood to investigate the death of an actor on a horror film set after rumors spread that he was killed by a ghost.
episodes.title: Hollywood Babylon

episodes.synopsis: After hearing about a ghost that has been killing off prison inmates one by one, Sam and Dean decide the best way to investigate is from the inside.
episodes.title: Folsom Prison Blues

episodes.synopsis: While hunting a djinn, or genie, Dean is attacked and transported to an alternate world.
episodes.title: What Is and What Should Never Be

episodes.synopsis: Sam is abducted by the yellow-eyed demon and finds himself in a ghost town with children who have special abilities.
episodes.title: All Hell Breaks Loose: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: While dealing with the aftermath of the fight between Sam and Jake, Dean pays a steep price for his involvement.
episodes.title: All Hell Breaks Loose: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean realize they have an enormous task: hunting down the hundreds of demons that escaped from the Devil's Gate.
episodes.title: The Magnificent Seven

episodes.synopsis: Dean pressures Sam into traveling to Cicero, Ind., so Dean can visit an old flame named Lisa, with whom he had a tryst nine years ago.
episodes.title: The Kids Are Alright

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean answer a call on their father's old cell phone, alerting them that someone has broken into their dad's secret storage room in New York.
episodes.title: Bad Day at Black Rock

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a rash of violent deaths in Elizabethville, Ohio, a once-sleepy town that has become a haven for gamblers and drinkers.
episodes.title: Sin City

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a small town that has been plagued by a number of strange murders mimicking fairy tales.
episodes.title: Bedtime Stories

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the mysterious demise of drowning victims who were nowhere near water at the time of their death.
episodes.title: Red Sky at Morning

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean capture a female vampire named Lucy who claims to have no knowledge of how she became a vampire.
episodes.title: Fresh Blood

episodes.synopsis: It's Christmastime, and Sam and Dean investigate a series of murders where the victims were pulled up through chimneys.
episodes.title: A Very Supernatural Christmas

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean travel to Sturbridge, Mass., and discover a coven of witches that has killed two people.
episodes.title: Malleus Maleficarum

episodes.synopsis: When Bobby falls into a coma and can't be awakened, Sam and Dean race to his side.
episodes.title: Dream a Little Dream of Me

episodes.synopsis: While Sam and Dean are investigating the disappearance of a man from a tourist location, Dean is shot and killed.
episodes.title: Mystery Spot

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean break into Bela's apartment in order to get the Colt back, but she has tipped off Agent Henricksen to their whereabouts.
episodes.title: Jus in Bello

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean stumble into starring roles on a gritty reality show called "Ghostfacers," which chronicles the pursuit of the paranormal.
episodes.title: Ghostfacers!

episodes.synopsis: Dean is stunned to receive a phone call from his dad, who says he has a solution to get Dean out of his deal.
episodes.title: Long-Distance Call

episodes.synopsis: As time runs out for Dean, Sam convinces him to head to Erie, Pa., to investigate a possible zombie case.
episodes.title: Time is on My Side

episodes.synopsis: In a battle to the death, Sam, Dean and Bob take on Lilith and all her demons in a last-ditch effort to save Dean's life.
episodes.title: No Rest for The Wicked

episodes.synopsis: Dean wakes up in a pine box, freed from Hell. He has a joyful reunion with Sam but they wonder what pulled Dean from Hell -- and why.
episodes.title: Lazarus Rising

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are stunned when the spirits of Meg and Agent Henricksen appear.
episodes.title: Are You There, God? It's Me, Dean Winchester

episodes.synopsis: Dean is transported back in time and finds that his newfound grandfather may be hiding a secret that is key to Sam and Dean's predicament.
episodes.title: In the Beginning

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean find that a family man is turning into a flesh-eating monster, and they argue about killing him.
episodes.title: Metamorphosis

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Sam investigate murders at Oktoberfest. Dean determines a shape-shifter demon is appearing as iconic monsters from old Hollywood movies.
episodes.title: Monster Movie

episodes.synopsis: Dean is infected with an illness that starts as anxiety, but moves to full-blown terror and stops the heart.
episodes.title: Yellow Fever

episodes.synopsis: The brothers deduce a witch is sacrificing people to summon a dangerous demon. Robert Wisdom guest stars as Uriel, a specialist angel.
episodes.title: It's the Great Pumpkin, Sam Winchester

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a small town where a wishing well actually works. The brothers realize, however, that the end result could be disastrous.
episodes.title: Wishful Thinking

episodes.synopsis: Ruby, Sam and Dean look for a girl who hears the angels. Castiel and Uriel return.
episodes.title: I Know What You Did Last Summer

episodes.synopsis: Anna recalls her past and Sam and Dean understand why Castiel and Uriel want her dead.
episodes.title: Heaven and Hell

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the appearance of a young female ghost in an abandoned house, but things become more complicated when a family moves in.
episodes.title: Family Remains

episodes.synopsis: Barry Bostwick, John Rubenstein and Richard Libertini guest star as three friends who used to be famous magicians but have since been replaced.
episodes.title: Criss Angel is a Douche Bag

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean go undercover at their old high school, causing them to flash back to when Sam was picked on by the school bully and Dean was popular.
episodes.title: After School Special

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean find three small-town men have beaten their wives to death. Behind the murders is a siren, who puts the brothers under her spell.
episodes.title: Sex and Violence

episodes.synopsis: Pamela sends the boys to the spiritual world when they find people cheating death. They must face Alastair, who is kidnapping the Reapers.
episodes.title: Death Takes a Holiday

episodes.synopsis: Castiel and Uriel capture Alastair, and ask Dean to torture him with skills he learned in Hell.
episodes.title: On the Head of a Pin

episodes.synopsis: What if the Winchesters weren't hunters? In this alternate life, Dean is a corporate man who enjoys health drinks and Sam is in tech support.
episodes.title: It's a Terrible Life

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean discover "Supernatural," a series of comic books that accurately detail their lives as demon hunters.
episodes.title: The Monster at the End of This Book

episodes.synopsis: A 19-year-old boy named Adam calls Sam and Dean looking for John Winchester; the boy claims to be his son.
episodes.title: Jump the Shark

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Sam search for Castiel, who appeared to Dean in a dream. Instead, they find Castiel's human vessel, who has little memory of being an angel.
episodes.title: The Rapture

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Bobby lock Sam in Bobby's panic room so he can detox from the demon blood. Sam and Dean have a big blowout confrontation.
episodes.title: When the Levee Breaks

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean prepare for the apocalypse in different ways. Ruby, Lilith, Castiel and Zachariah appear.
episodes.title: Lucifer Rising

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Sam watch as the devil emerges from hell and must deal with the aftermath.
episodes.title: Sympathy for the Devil

episodes.synopsis: While Castiel goes in search of God in the fight against Lucifer, Sam and Dean help an old hunter friend of Bobby's.
episodes.title: Good God, Y'all!

episodes.synopsis: Not sure he trusts himself anymore, Sam decides to give up hunting. Meanwhile, Dean teams up with Castiel to find the Archangel Raphael.
episodes.title: Free to Be You and Me

episodes.synopsis: Dean gets a glimpse of the future in which humans have been infected with a demonic virus that turns them into zombies.
episodes.title: The End

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean reunite to investigate a small town whose inhabitants are being killed by famous dead people.
episodes.title: Fallen Idols

episodes.synopsis: Investigating a series of odd murders that resemble fairy tales and urban legends, Sam and Dean track down a dangerous boy named Jesse.
episodes.title: I Believe the Children Are Our Future

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean play a high-stakes poker game with a witch where the currency is life years -- not money.
episodes.title: The Curious Case of Dean Winchester

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean get stuck in TV Hell when the Trickster imprisons them in an alternate universe.
episodes.title: Changing Channels

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean attend a "Supernatural" fan convention -- complete with fans dressed up as Sam and Dean.
episodes.title: The Real Ghostbusters

episodes.synopsis: It's a hunters' reunion when Sam and Dean face off against Lucifer with the help of Castiel, Bobby, Ellen and Jo.
episodes.title: Abandon All Hope

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean check into a mental hospital to investigate a mysterious monster that's been attacking the patients.
episodes.title: Sam, Interrupted

episodes.synopsis: A teenage nerd conjures up a body-switching spell and changes bodies with Sam.
episodes.title: Swap Meat

episodes.synopsis: The angels go back in time to kill John and Mary Winchester before they can conceive Sam.
episodes.title: The Song Remains the Same

episodes.synopsis: Castiel helps Sam and Dean hunt down Cupid on Valentine's Day after people begin killing each other for love.
episodes.title: My Bloody Valentine

episodes.synopsis: The dead are rising from their graves and happily reuniting with their families in Bobby's hometown.
episodes.title: Dead Men Don't Wear Plaid

episodes.synopsis: Ambushed by angry hunters, Sam and Dean are shot and killed and sent to heaven!
episodes.title: Dark Side of the Moon

episodes.synopsis: Outnumbered by demons, Sam and Dean are saved at the last minute by a hunter and his very religious townspeople.
episodes.title: 99 Problems

episodes.synopsis: When Dean learns that the angels have decided they don't need him anymore, he joins with Sam and Castiel to take on Zachariah.
episodes.title: Point of No Return

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are held hostage by a group of gods who want to use them as bargaining chips to stop the apocalypse.
episodes.title: Hammer of the Gods

episodes.synopsis: The demon Crowley offers to help Sam and Dean find the remaining Horsemen by leading them to the Handler for Pestilence and Death.
episodes.title: The Devil You Know

episodes.synopsis: Bobby sells his soul to the demon Crowley in exchange for the location of the Fourth Horseman.
episodes.title: Two Minutes to Midnight

episodes.synopsis: With the apocalypse looming in a showdown between good and evil, Sam and Dean realize they are out of options.
episodes.title: Swan Song

episodes.synopsis: Mysteriously freed from hell, Sam finds Dean and tells him he needs to rejoin the fight.
episodes.title: Exile on Main St.

episodes.synopsis: Sam investigates a case involving missing babies whose parents are being murdered.
episodes.title: Two and a Half Men

episodes.synopsis: Investigating a case of biblical plagues, Sam and Dean call Castiel for help and learn that God's weapons have been stolen.
episodes.title: The Third Man

episodes.synopsis: After Bobby discovers Crowley has no intentions of returning Bobby's soul, the hunter takes matters into his own hands.
episodes.title: Weekend at Bobby's

episodes.synopsis: After fighting a group of vampires, Dean is bitten and turns into a vampire.
episodes.title: Live Free or Twi-hard

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a series of suicides and discover that someone is invoking the Goddess of Truth, forcing people to be cruelly honest.
episodes.title: You Can't Handle the Truth

episodes.synopsis: Dean becomes suspicious of Samuel's motives when the brothers go along on a hunt with their grandfather and the other Campbells and things go awry.
episodes.title: Family Matters

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Sam investigate a werewolf killing that turns out to be a skinwalker posing as a family dog who is taking revenge on his owner's enemies.
episodes.title: All Dogs Go to Heaven

episodes.synopsis: While Sam and Dean are investigating a UFO sighting, Dean is abducted from a crop circle.
episodes.title: Clap Your Hands if You Believe

episodes.synopsis: The demon Meg kidnaps Sam and Dean for information on Crowley. Sam offers to help her if she'll help get his soul back.
episodes.title: Caged Heat

episodes.synopsis: Dean makes a deal with Death to help get Sam's soul back, but Sam decides that he doesn't want it back and enlists help to keep it that way.
episodes.title: Appointment in Samarra

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Bobby investigate the disappearance of virgins and discover dragons are behind the kidnapping.
episodes.title: Like a Virgin

episodes.synopsis: When Sam receives a mysterious text with coordinates to a small town, he starts to have flashbacks to an old case.
episodes.title: Unforgiven

episodes.synopsis: When Ben calls Dean and tells him that Lisa is in trouble, Dean leaves Sam to investigate a case alone and rushes to the rescue.
episodes.title: Mannequin 3: The Reckoning

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are transported to an alternate reality where they are the stars of a TV show called "Supernatural."
episodes.title: The French Mistake

episodes.synopsis: In search of the Mother of All's latest monster, Sam, Dean and Bobby run into Samuel and Gwen Campbell and fight about how to handle the case.
episodes.title: ...And Then There Were None

episodes.synopsis: Castiel tells Sam and Dean that Fate is very upset with the two of them and the only way they can stay alive is to kill her.
episodes.title: My Heart Will Go On

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are sent back in time to the Wild West so they can meet Samuel Colt and ask him for his help in defeating Eve.
episodes.title: Frontierland

episodes.synopsis: Sam, Dean, Bobby and Castiel track Eve to a small Oregon town, where she's transforming the inhabitants into demons.
episodes.title: Mommy Dearest

episodes.synopsis: Castiel tells Sam, Dean and Bobby about the war in heaven and how he and Raphael became enemies.
episodes.title: The Man Who Would Be King

episodes.synopsis: Dean's worst nightmare comes true when a demon kidnaps Ben and Lisa to get to him.
episodes.title: Let It Bleed

episodes.synopsis: The wall comes down in Sam's mind and all hell breaks loose, while Dean and Bobby are powerless to help. The battle for heaven comes to a head.
episodes.title: The Man Who Knew Too Much

episodes.synopsis: Assuming his new role as God, Castiel sets out to right some of the wrongs in the world. And Dean decides to bind Death in order to stop him.
episodes.title: Meet the New Boss

episodes.synopsis: While Castiel struggles with the burdens of his absolute power, the broken psychological wall in Sam's mind leaves him unable to discern what's real.
episodes.title: Hello, Cruel World

episodes.synopsis: Dean is furious when Sam disappears to follow a case with clues identical to a case Sam solved as a kid. And Sam meets a demon he defeated years ago.
episodes.title: The Girl Next Door

episodes.synopsis: Investigating a string of gruesome murders, Sam and Dean discover the vengeful Egyptian god Osiris, who puts Dean on trial for his past mistakes.
episodes.title: Defending Your Life

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean track down a witch who's taking out her wrath for her unfaithful husband on the entire town.
episodes.title: Shut Up, Dr. Phil

episodes.synopsis: Once again on the FBI's "Most Wanted" list, Sam and Dean seek help from a friend of Bobby's when two Leviathans go on a killing spree as Sam and Dean.
episodes.title: Slash Fiction

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate an angry spirit killing the resident mediums of Lily Dale, the most "psychic" town in America.
episodes.title: The Mentalists

episodes.synopsis: While Sam's entangled with someone from his past, Dean reluctantly teams up with a quirky laidback hunter named Garth.
episodes.title: Season 7, Time for a Wedding!

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean track the Jersey Devil, a creature suspected of attacking people in the woods, and encounter a monster sandwich with nasty side effects.
episodes.title: How to Win Friends and Influence Monsters

episodes.synopsis: Bobby seeks the help of an unlikely old friend to solve one of the most personal cases of his life.
episodes.title: Death's Door

episodes.synopsis: While Dean becomes obsessed with eliminating Dick Roman, Sam helps a teenage girl look for her father, a hunter who's gone missing.
episodes.title: Adventures In Babysitting

episodes.synopsis: The God of Time who sends Dean back to 1944, where he is immediately arrested by the legendary Eliot Ness who, surprisingly, is also a hunter.
episodes.title: Time After Time

episodes.synopsis: Dean's rendezvous with an Amazon warrior has serious complications!
episodes.title: The Slice Girls

episodes.synopsis: Sam confronts his fear of clowns when he and Dean investigate a children's pizza chain that's manifesting children's worst (and deadliest) fears.
episodes.title: Plucky Pennywhistle's Magic Menagerie

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the apparent reappearance of a demon they exorcised years ago.
episodes.title: Repo Man

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean visit a town gone haywire after a large collection of cursed objects is mistakenly released.
episodes.title: Out With the Old

episodes.synopsis: Desperate to save Sam from Lucifer, Dean calls every hunter for help, but instead meets a healer with a familiar face.
episodes.title: The Born-Again Identity

episodes.synopsis: Garth needs the Winchesters' help on a case, battling a Shojo -- a Japanese creature sent to seek revenge on enemies.
episodes.title: Party On, Garth

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean get a call from a hunter friend, Annie, asking for help on a case. They arrive town only to discover that Annie is missing.
episodes.title: Of Grave Importance

episodes.synopsis: An unsuspecting, but hip hacker is hired by Dick Roman to break through Frank's firewall and gain information on the Winchesters.
episodes.title: The Girl With the Dungeons and Dragons Tattoo

episodes.synopsis: At the same time that Castiel emerges from his comatose state, a young boy emerges as a reluctant prophet -- with the key to defeating Leviathans.
episodes.title: Reading is Fundamental

episodes.synopsis: To defeat Dick Roman and the Leviathans, Sam and Dean must locate three key items that must be retrieved from Castiel, Crowley and an Alpha Vampire!
episodes.title: There Will Be Blood

episodes.synopsis: In order to stop Dick Roman and the Leviathans, Sam and Dean must team up with Castiel, Bobby, Meg and the prophet Kevin to storm SucroCorp.
episodes.title: Survival of the Fittest

episodes.synopsis: After escaping from Purgatory (but not alone), Dean heads straight for Sam, but the reunion isn't exactly everything he imagined it would be.
episodes.title: We Need to Talk About Kevin

episodes.synopsis: Checking in on Kevin's mom, the Winchesters discover that Crowley has surrounded her with demons, so they save her and take her along on their quest.
episodes.title: What's Up, Tiger Mommy?

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate a string of unusual murders in which the victims were all recipients of organs from the same donor.
episodes.title: Heartache

episodes.synopsis: Close on the tail of their suspect, Sam and Dean bust into an apartment to find two dead bodies and a laptop cued up to some disturbing video footage.
episodes.title: Bitten

episodes.synopsis: After Dean's vampire companion in Purgatory, Benny, gets brutally beat up by his own kind, he calls Dean for help in going after his maker.
episodes.title: Blood Brother

episodes.synopsis: Investigating a murder, Sam and Dean find that Garth is already on the case. Garth says since the brothers went missing, someone needed to step up.
episodes.title: Southern Comfort

episodes.synopsis: Castiel suddenly appears back on Earth with no memory of how he escaped from Purgatory. Mrs. Tran enlists a witch to concoct a demon bomb.
episodes.title: A Little Slice of Kevin

episodes.synopsis: After learning that Castiel plans to be a hunter, Sam and Dean join him in investigating a case where a man's heart literally burst through his chest.
episodes.title: Hunteri Heroici

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are at odds after Sam asks a hunter named Martin to keep an eye on Benny without telling Dean.
episodes.title: Citizen Fang

episodes.synopsis: Naomi tells Castiel that Crowley is holding an angel captive, and Castiel must rescue him before Crowley's torture reveals their secrets.
episodes.title: Torn and Frayed

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the mysterious deaths of two LARPers (Live Action Role Players) who were engaged in a game involving an actual fairy.
episodes.title: LARP and the Real Girl

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are stunned when a man who claims to be their grandfather, Henry Winchester, suddenly appears to stop a demon named Abbadon.
episodes.title: As Time Goes By

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate the death of a rabbi who spontaneously combusted. They soon learn that the rabbi was researching Nazi Necromancers.
episodes.title: Everybody Hates Hitler

episodes.synopsis: Kevin finally deciphers the God tablet, telling Sam and Dean that one person must face a series of three tests designed by God.
episodes.title: Trial and Error

episodes.synopsis: A police officer, who turned to witchcraft after working a case with Sam and Dean, is plagued by nightmares in which he murders innocent people.
episodes.title: Man's Best Friend with Benefits

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are stumped when they investigate a possible zombie case where an amnesiac man dies and then revives himself once a day.
episodes.title: Remember the Titans

episodes.synopsis: Castiel tells Sam and Dean that Crowley has unleashed several demons into a small town to search for Lucifer's Crypt, which holds a valuable asset.
episodes.title: Goodbye Stranger

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean investigate some recent vampire kills and are surprised to learn that teenage hunter Krissy Chambers is involved.
episodes.title: Freaks and Geeks

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean respond to Kevin, who is hearing Crowley's voice in his head. They later team up with a reaper to deal with the tablet's second trial.
episodes.title: Taxi Driver

episodes.synopsis: Concerned about the toll the second trial took on Sam, Dean benches his brother until he heals up. Dean teaches Charlie to be a hunter-in-training.
episodes.title: Pac-Man Fever

episodes.synopsis: After receiving a message from Kevin, Sam and Dean try to uncover the third trial. The boys make a discovery that sends them to a casino in Colorado.
episodes.title: The Great Escapist

episodes.synopsis: As the third trial nears, Sam and Dean reunite with Castiel. They stumble upon an undiscovered film, which could be the key to the third trial.
episodes.title: Clip Show

episodes.synopsis: What must Sam, Dean and Castiel sacrifice to seal the gates of Hell? With Kevin's help, the Winchester brothers have one last play against Crowley.
episodes.title: Sacrifice

episodes.synopsis: Devastated by Sam's collapse, Dean makes a pact with Ezekiel while his brother fights to live. Meanwhile, Castiel struggles to survive without powers.
episodes.title: I Think I'm Gonna Like It Here

episodes.synopsis: Dean shocks Sam when he opens the Impala's trunk to reveal he's kidnapped the King of Hell. Meanwhile, Abaddon rises with plans to take over his role.
episodes.title: Devil May Care

episodes.synopsis: After Ezekiel tells Dean a group of angels is hunting Castiel, he and Sam race to find their friend before the vengeful angels do.
episodes.title: I'm No Angel

episodes.synopsis: The brothers call in IT expert Charlie to help them track fallen angels, and they all join forces with Dorothy to stop the Wicked Witch's evil plans.
episodes.title: Slumber Party

episodes.synopsis: After a series of killings by a murderer with animal traits, Dean casts a spell to communicate with a German Shepherd -- with unfortunate side effects.
episodes.title: Dog Dean Afternoon

episodes.synopsis: Dean and Castiel investigate a series of spontaneous human combustions, while Crowley helps Sam and Kevin translate an ancient tablet.
episodes.title: Heaven Can't Wait

episodes.synopsis: When an old friend of Dean's asks him to help solve a murder, Sam learns that Dean has a secret past -- one that will help them solve the crime.
episodes.title: Bad Boys

episodes.synopsis: Sheriff Mills calls the brothers to help solve the murder of a church chastity group's members. They infiltrate the group, then Dean disappears.
episodes.title: Rock and a Hard Place

episodes.synopsis: The angel war begins, so Sam, Dean and Castiel investigate; Castiel is captured and Dean wonders if he needs to come clean to Sam about Ezekiel.
episodes.title: Holy Terror

episodes.synopsis: Gadreel is still in control of Sam's body while on a murder spree for Metatron, but Dean, Castiel and Crowley have plans for an angel eviction.
episodes.title: Road Trip

episodes.synopsis: Hoping to kill mutual enemy Abaddon, Dean and Crowley search for the "First Blade" and are stunned to find out its owner is Cain, the first son.
episodes.title: First Born

episodes.synopsis: Garth is in the hospital after mutilating a cow and being hit by a car. They try to help him, but Garth runs away -- with a dark secret in tow.
episodes.title: Sharp Teeth

episodes.synopsis: The Winchesters head to a health spa where guests wind up dead -- and hundreds of pounds lighter. Sam and Dean suspect fat-sucking witchcraft.
episodes.title: The Purge

episodes.synopsis: Sam and Dean are stunned to discover that the Men of Letters's bunker is haunted. Meanwhile, Castiel is captured by Bartholomew.
episodes.title: Captives

episodes.synopsis: When a teenage girl is killed, the final selfie she took before the attack shows a shadowy figure in the background. Can Dean and Sam find the ghost?
episodes.title: #thinman

episodes.synopsis: When Crowley confesses he's been injecting human blood, Sam and Dean enlist the help of a former member of the Men of Letters to find the First Blade.
episodes.title: Blade Runners

episodes.synopsis: With Sam looking into a town where good people are turning into violent killers, Dean confronts the aftereffects of having the Mark of Cain.
episodes.title: Mother's Little Helper

episodes.synopsis: Metatron tries to persuade Castiel to join him, and the Winchesters finally capture Gadreel, who tries to play Dean's Mark of Cain against him.
episodes.title: Meta Fiction

episodes.synopsis: When a prisoner is attacked by a vampire, Sheriff Mills calls Sam and Dean, who discover the victim was kidnapped by an entire vampire family.
episodes.title: Alex Annie Alexis Ann

episodes.synopsis: The brothers investigate stories of Mafia-like monster families living under Chicago's streets and meet Ennis, a would-be hunter of monsters.
episodes.title: Bloodlines

episodes.synopsis: Castiel captures one of Metatron's angels and asks Sam and Dean for help. Meanwhile, Abaddon demands that Crowley help her kill Sam and Dean.
episodes.title: King of the Damned

episodes.synopsis: After a massive attack on the angels, Castiel calls the brothers for help. But Dean's eagerness to bring the First Blade doesn't go unnoticed.
episodes.title: Stairway to Heaven

episodes.synopsis: Dean feels the effects of the First Blade, and Metatron makes his move against humanity. Meanwhile, Sam, Dean and Castiel face shocking consequences.
episodes.title: Do You Believe in Miracles?
